data.title: Famous People From Quezon City, Philippines & Celebs Born In Quezon City
data.meta_description: Quezon City has produced a number of famous personalities, including actresses, actors, models etc.
data.text:
1

Nadine Lustre

(Filipino Actress and Singer Known for Her Role as ‘Eya Rodriguez’ in the Film ‘Diary ng Panget’)

52

16

Listed In: Film & Theater Personalities

Birthdate: October 31, 1993

Sun Sign: Scorpio

Nadine Lustre is a Filipina actress, music video director, and singer best known for her portrayal of Eya Rodriguez in the 2014 romantic comedy film, Diary ng Panget. One of the most decorated Filipina celebrities, Lustre has won several prestigious awards, such as the Young Critics Circle award, Asian Academy Creative Award, Myx Music Awards, and Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Award.

While he considers Hello, Love, Goodbye, the highest-grossing Filipino film ever, as his best project so far, actor Alden Richards has had a long career, peppered with films, music, and more. He will now be seen with Bea Alonzo in a film based on the Japanese series Pure Soul.

Coco Martin

(Actor)

115

53

Listed In: Film & Theater Personalities

Birthdate: November 1, 1981

Sun Sign: Scorpio

Coco Martin is a Filipino actor, director, and producer. He is best known for his lead role in the film Minsan Lang Kita Iibigin. He began acting in the early 2000s with small roles in TV shows. In the ensuing years, he moved on to more serious roles in TV series and films. He made his directorial debut in 2017.

Alex Eala is a Filipino professional tennis player best known for winning the US Open Junior title in 2022. Eala first achieved popularity in 2020, when she won the Australian Open Junior Doubles title. The following year, Alex Eala won the French Open Junior Doubles title. In 2021, she also won three bronze medals at the Southeast Asian Games.

Filipino politician Ralph Recto is the current Deputy Speaker of the House of Representatives and represents the 6th district of Batangas. The Nacionalista member has also been a senator of the Philippines and a Senate Minority Leader. He has also represented Lakas-CMD and LDP. He is married to actor-politician Vilma Santos-Recto.

0

Listed In: Sportspersons

Birthdate: March 16, 2000

Justin Baas is a Filipino football player who plays as a defender for the Philippines national team and Melaka United, which competes in the Malaysia Super League. Born to a Filipino mother and a Dutch father, Baas was eligible to play for both the Philippines and Netherlands. Justin Baas represented the Netherlands U15 national team before playing for the Philippines.
